                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.156/256</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-26T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 24, 11 a.m. You are instructed to congratulate the President upon his
                    having been authorized by Congress to settle the Ports Company matter, and you
                    will add that this Government now feels assured that a just and prompt
                    settlement will be forthcoming.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
